news.title: Commercial plots on offer near Jewar airport site
news.para: YEIDA has expedited work on a slew of schemes starting with the commercial and industrial plot schemes, even as final touches are being given to around 450 residential plot scheme proposed in Sector 16 of YEIDA.

news.title: Saint Gobain wants to triple revenues to Rs 30,000 crore in 10 years
news.para: Saint Gobain’s plaster boards, construction chemicals that are used as additives in ready mix concrete, fasad, insulators and ceilings are witnessing strong demand from the construction sector.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing's promoter sells 11.9% stake to make it professionally managed firm
news.para: "With this sale, I and my promoter companies now own 9.8 per cent of the company. I intend to hold these shares and participate in the future growth story of the company," Indiabulls Housing Finance quoted Gehlaut as saying in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Mumbai: Adani, L&T and Naman Developers bid for Motilal Nagar redevelopment
news.para: Two top developers, Godrej Properties and Bengaluru-based Prestige Group, formally protested and wrote to Mhada about a controversial clause in the tender which makes most builders ineligible for the huge contract.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks police to produce senior management of Sepset Properties & Supertech
news.para: According to K K Khandelwal, both the companies have not be responding to notices of the authority and not complying with the orders issued by it.

news.title: New York City moves to stop new buildings from using natural gas
news.para: If Democratic Mayor Bill de Blasio signs the measure, as expected, most construction projects submitted for approval after 2027 would have to use something other than gas or oil - such as electricity - for heating, hot water and cooking. Some smaller buildings would have to comply as early as 2024.

news.title: Singapore tightens curbs to cool buoyant property market
news.para: Private housing prices have risen by about 9% since the first quarter of 2020, while public housing resale flat prices have increased about 15%.

news.title: China Fortune Land says 'has lost touch' with company it gave $300 million
news.para: China Fortune Land Development said in a filing to the Shanghai Stock Exchange that it had recently "lost contact" with China Create Capital after handing over the money in 2018.

news.title: USA: Evictions on the rise months after federal moratorium ends
news.para: The federal ban, along with a mix of state and federal moratoriums, is credited with keeping Davis and millions of others in their homes during the pandemic and preventing the spread of the coronavirus.

news.title: Paranjape Group gets Rs 105 crore investment in two housing projects
news.para: Both these projects are part of Paranjape group's township Blueridge, which is spread over 138 acres. The township has an operational SEZ of around 3 million square feet, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Lavasa creditors start voting on two resolution proposals
news.para: Darwin Platform has offered Rs 929 crore to be paid over 140 months, inclusive of 6% interest, without any upfront cash payment to lenders, said one of the persons quoted above.

news.title: Cidco tells Panvel civic body to take over physical infrastructure services by Dec 20
news.para: Cidco's letter dated December 13 by chief engineer Dr KM Godbole to Panvel civic chief Ganesh Deshmukh states that PCMC should take over the charge by December 20, 2021, by mentioning that it was to avoid double taxation to citizens in PCMC area.

news.title: Pune: Activists fear property tax waiver misuse
news.para: The group on Wednesday wrote a letter to the Pune Municipal Corporation. “If the scheme is going to benefit the defaulters but fails to discipline them, it should then be scrapped,” the activists’ group stated.

news.title: Square Yards plans Rs 1,500 crore IPO; to soon file draft paper with Sebi
news.para: Market sources said that Square Yards is planning to launch its IPO with an issue size of about Rs 1,500 crore. The issue would be a mix of fresh issuance and offer for sale (OFS) for existing shareholders.

news.title: PropReturns raises $1.2 million funding from Y Combinator, others
news.para: Kenish Shah, co-founder of the company said, "We aim to solve an aspect of the real estate market that has not been addressed yet."
